	<dita:topic xmlns="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="UK11_DA_dig.type">
    <title>dig:type <lnpid>id-UK11DA-29448</lnpid></title>
    <body>
        <section>
            <p><sourcexml>dig:type</sourcexml> becomes
                    <targetxml>abstract:head/classify:classification[@classscheme="sourcetype"]/classify:classitem/classify:classitem-identifier/classify:classname</targetxml>.</p></section>
        <note><targetxml>abstract:head</targetxml> is a required child of
                <targetxml>abstract:abstract</targetxml>. Source <sourcexml>dig:cite</sourcexml>,
                <sourcexml>leg:dates</sourcexml>, <sourcexml>leg:govoffice</sourcexml>,
                <sourcexml>leg:categories</sourcexml>, and <sourcexml>dig:type</sourcexml> map
            within <targetxml>abstract:head</targetxml>. If none is present, create
                <targetxml>abstract:head</targetxml> as an empty element.</note>
        <!-- McNally Mar 16 2015. The values can be very broad, e.g. Quasi-Legal General, or very specific, e.g. HMRC Press Release. 
            In all cases the value represents a category that Lexis has chosen. For that reason, not placing within the abstract:target because not strictly source metadata. 
        Product intends for the values to be searchable and displayed so not placing in doc.metadata.  Similar data added to UK11-DN and also targeting head portion. -->
        <pre>
              <b><i>Example: Source XML 1</i></b>
                  

&lt;dig:body&gt;
    &lt;dig:info&gt;
        &lt;dig:type&gt;Quasi-Legal General&lt;/dig:type&gt;
    &lt;/dig:info&gt;
&lt;/dig:body&gt;
 
	</pre>
        <pre>
                    
              <b><i>Example: Target XML 1</i></b>
    
&lt;abstract:head&gt;
    &lt;classify:classification classscheme="sourcetype"&gt;
        &lt;classify:classitem&gt;
            &lt;classify:classitem-identifier&gt;
                &lt;classify:classname&gt;Quasi-Legal General&lt;/classify:classname&gt;
            &lt;/classify:classitem-identifier&gt;
        &lt;/classify:classitem&gt;
    &lt;/classify:classification&gt;
&lt;/abstract:head&gt;

                </pre>

